parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent acceleration failure can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto a highway or when trying to pass another vehicle. It can also cause loss of control, leading to crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate when the accelerator is depressed
or lurches forward while applying the brake. The vehicle may also stall or hesitate to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, especially when the vehicle is in motion. It can cause loss of control, leading to crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without the driver's input. The vehicle may also surge forward while the driver is attempting to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failure to engage can lead to accidents, especially when merging onto a highway or when trying to pass another vehicle. It can also cause loss of control, leading to crashes or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle's transmission slips or fails to engage
causing the vehicle to hesitate or lurch forward. The vehicle may also stall or hesitate to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator position switch can cause sluggish acceleration, loss of power, and unpredictable vehicle behavior, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: delayed response to accelerator pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the airbags not deploying in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbag system is no longer operable
the airbag control switch needs to be replaced
the airbag light remains off when someone is sitting in the passenger seat.
